{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"LinearAccelerationSensor","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/LinearAccelerationSensor","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","browserCompat":["api.LinearAccelerationSensor"],"baseline":{"baseline":false,"support":{"chrome":"91","chrome_android":"91","edge":"91"}},"sidebarHTML":"<ol><li class=\"section\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor_APIs\">Sensor APIs</a></li><li class=\"section\"><em><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/LinearAccelerationSensor\" aria-current=\"page\"><code>LinearAccelerationSensor</code></a></em></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/LinearAccelerationSensor/LinearAccelerationSensor\"><code>LinearAccelerationSensor()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Accelerometer\"><code>Accelerometer</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor\"><code>Sensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\"><code>EventTarget</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Sensor API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AbsoluteOrientationSensor\"><code>AbsoluteOrientationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Accelerometer\"><code>Accelerometer</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/AmbientLightSensor\"><code>AmbientLightSensor</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/GravitySensor\"><code>GravitySensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Gyroscope\"><code>Gyroscope</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Magnetometer\"><code>Magnetometer</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/OrientationSensor\"><code>OrientationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/RelativeOrientationSensor\"><code>RelativeOrientationSensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor\"><code>Sensor</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/SensorErrorEvent\"><code>SensorErrorEvent</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","sidebarMacro":"APIRef","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard secure\"><p><strong>Secure context:</strong> This feature is available only in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Secure_Contexts\">secure contexts</a> (HTTPS), in some or all <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">supporting browsers</a>.</p></div>\n<p>The <strong><code>LinearAccelerationSensor</code></strong> interface of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor_APIs\">Sensor APIs</a> provides on each reading the acceleration applied to the device along all three axes, but without the contribution of gravity.</p>\n<p>To use this sensor, the user must grant permission to the <code>'accelerometer'</code> device sensor through the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Permissions_API\">Permissions API</a>. In addition, this feature may be blocked by a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Permissions_Policy\">Permissions Policy</a> set on your server.</p><svg viewBox=\"-1 -1 650 42\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMinYMin meet\">\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\">\n    <rect x=\"0\" y=\"0\" width=\"88\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#fff\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"44\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      EventTarget\n    </text>\n  </a>\n  <line x1=\"88\" y1=\"14\" x2=\"118\" y2=\"14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\"></line>\n  <polyline points=\"88,14 98,9 98,19 88,14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" fill=\"#fff\"></polyline>\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor\">\n    <rect x=\"118\" y=\"0\" width=\"75\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#fff\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"155.5\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      Sensor\n    </text>\n  </a>\n  <line x1=\"193\" y1=\"14\" x2=\"223\" y2=\"14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\"></line>\n  <polyline points=\"193,14 203,9 203,19 193,14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" fill=\"#fff\"></polyline>\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Accelerometer\">\n    <rect x=\"223\" y=\"0\" width=\"104\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#fff\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"275\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      Accelerometer\n    </text>\n  </a>\n  <line x1=\"327\" y1=\"14\" x2=\"357\" y2=\"14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\"></line>\n  <polyline points=\"327,14 337,9 337,19 327,14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" fill=\"#fff\"></polyline>\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/LinearAccelerationSensor\" aria-current=\"page\">\n    <rect x=\"357\" y=\"0\" width=\"192\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#F4F7F8\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"453\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      LinearAccelerationSensor\n    </text>\n  </a></svg>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"constructor","title":"Constructor","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"linearaccelerationsensor\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/LinearAccelerationSensor/LinearAccelerationSensor\" title=\"LinearAccelerationSensor()\"><code>LinearAccelerationSensor()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Creates a new <code>LinearAccelerationSensor</code> object.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"instance_properties","title":"Instance properties","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em>Inherits properties from its ancestors, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Accelerometer\"><code>Accelerometer</code></a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor\"><code>Sensor</code></a>, and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\"><code>EventTarget</code></a>.</em></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"instance_methods","title":"Instance methods","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em><code>LinearAccelerationSensor</code> doesn't have own methods. However, it inherits methods from its parent interfaces, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor\"><code>Sensor</code></a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\"><code>EventTarget</code></a>.</em></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"events","title":"Events","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em><code>LinearAccelerationSensor</code> doesn't have own events. However, it inherits events from its parent interface, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor\"><code>Sensor</code></a>.</em></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example","title":"Example","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Linear acceleration is typically read in the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Sensor/reading_event\" title=\"reading\"><code>reading</code></a> event callback. In the example below this occurs sixty times a second.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><div class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></div><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>let laSensor = new LinearAccelerationSensor({ frequency: 60 });\n\nlaSensor.addEventListener(\"reading\", (e) =&gt; {\n  console.log(`Linear acceleration along the X-axis ${laSensor.x}`);\n  console.log(`Linear acceleration along the Y-axis ${laSensor.y}`);\n  console.log(`Linear acceleration along the Z-axis ${laSensor.z}`);\n});\nlaSensor.start();\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/accelerometer/#linearaccelerationsensor-interface","title":"Accelerometer"}],"query":"api.LinearAccelerationSensor"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.LinearAccelerationSensor"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Constructor","id":"constructor"},{"text":"Instance properties","id":"instance_properties"},{"text":"Instance methods","id":"instance_methods"},{"text":"Events","id":"events"},{"text":"Example","id":"example"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The LinearAccelerationSensor interface of the Sensor APIs provides on each reading the acceleration applied to the device along all three axes, but without the contribution of gravity.","popularity":0,"modified":"2020-11-30T15:24:28.344Z","other_translations":[],"pageType":"web-api-interface","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/linearaccelerationsensor","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/api/linearaccelerationsensor/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/null","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"LinearAccelerationSensor","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/LinearAccelerationSensor","title":"LinearAccelerationSensor"}],"pageTitle":"LinearAccelerationSensor - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false},"url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/LinearAccelerationSensor"}